# Build-context allowlist. The demo images build with `context: ..` (the repo root), so the
# Docker daemon would otherwise receive the whole repo. This is a DEFAULT-DENY allowlist:
# ignore everything (`*`), then un-ignore only the paths the Dockerfiles COPY, then re-exclude
# secrets and build-noise inside them. Net effect: no secret, seed dump, or local-only artifact
# (deploy/.env, demo_seed.sql, CLAUDE.md, COST_ANALYSIS.md, PRICING_STRATEGY.md, AUDIT_LOG.md,
# docs/, specs/, .venv, ...) can reach the build context or a future `COPY .` — and new local
# files are excluded by default, with no denylist to keep in sync.
#
# Safe because the wheel build packages only `src/outrider` (pyproject [tool.hatch.build...];
# no readme/license-file refs) and the Dockerfiles COPY explicit paths:
#   app (deploy/Dockerfile):      pyproject.toml uv.lock src/ db/ alembic.ini
#   web (deploy/Dockerfile.web):  dashboard/ deploy/Caddyfile
*

!src
!db
!dashboard
!deploy
!pyproject.toml
!uv.lock
!alembic.ini

# Re-exclude secrets / runtime files / build-noise within the un-ignored paths.
deploy/.env
deploy/.env.*
deploy/demo_seed.sql
dashboard/node_modules
dashboard/dist
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
